# HOW TO USE VS CODE

## WHAT IS VS CODE?

VS Code is the main coding software used for this project.

It is where:

• Files are edited
• Terminal is opened
• Backend runs
• Frontend runs

---

# HOW TO OPEN PROJECT

## STEP 1

Open VS Code.

---

## STEP 2

Click:

File → Open Folder

---

## STEP 3

Select:

A.U.R.A folder

---

# HOW TO OPEN TERMINAL

Inside VS Code:

Press:

CTRL + `

OR:

Terminal → New Terminal

This opens CMD/PowerShell inside VS Code.

---

# HOW TO RUN FRONTEND

Inside terminal:

cd frontend
npm run dev

Then open:

[http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

---

# HOW TO RUN BACKEND

Open NEW terminal.

Run:

cd backend
uvicorn main:app --reload

Then backend runs at:

[http://127.0.0.1:8000](http://127.0.0.1:8000)

---

# IMPORTANT

Frontend and backend BOTH must run at same time.

Two terminals are required.

---

# HOW TO DOWNLOAD EVERYTHING FROM GITHUB

## STEP 1

Install Git.

Download:

[https://git-scm.com/](https://git-scm.com/)

Install normally.

---

## STEP 2

Open terminal.

---

## STEP 3

Run:

git clone YOUR_GITHUB_REPO_LINK

Example:

git clone [https://github.com/username/AURA.git](https://github.com/username/AURA.git)

---

## STEP 4

Open cloned folder in VS Code.

---

# HOW TO INSTALL FRONTEND REQUIREMENTS

Inside terminal:

cd frontend
npm install

This installs:

• React
• Next.js
• TailwindCSS
• All frontend dependencies

---

# HOW TO INSTALL BACKEND REQUIREMENTS

## STEP 1

Open backend folder.

cd backend

---

## STEP 2

Create virtual environment.

python -m venv venv

---

## STEP 3

Activate virtual environment.

On Windows:

venv\Scripts\activate

---

## STEP 4

Install backend dependencies.

pip install ultralytics opencv-python fastapi uvicorn pillow numpy websockets

---

# HOW TO ADD YOLO MODEL

Download:

yolov8n.pt

Place it inside:

backend/models/

